The Asia Foundation PPA with DFID CHASE is helping to address common challenges to peaceful state-society relations in fragile states, subnational conflict and post-conflict areas and transitional states at risk of renewed conflict. This activity represents programs in Pakistan under the PPA during the period Oct-Dec 2011. These activities have the following objectives: More effective mechanisms for societal groups in fragile and transitional states to influence state policy and behaviour.;

The Asia Foundation PPA with DFID CHASE is helping to address common challenges to peaceful state-society relations in fragile states, subnational conflict and post-conflict areas and transitional states at risk of renewed conflict. This activity represents programs in Timor-Leste under the PPA during the period Oct-Dec 2011. These activities have the following objectives: 1) More effective mechanisms for societal groups in fragile and transitional states to influence state policy and behavior; 2) Expanded community-level efforts to improve local security and relations with security forces (police, military).;

he Asia Foundation PPA with DFID CHASE is helping to address common challenges to peaceful state-society relations in fragile states, subnational conflict and post-conflict areas and transitional states at risk of renewed conflict. This activity represents programs in Myanmar under the PPA during the period Jul-Sep 2014. These activities have the following objective: Governance reforms implemented to reduce grievances of conflict-affected populations in subnational conflict areas.;

PH: The Asia Foundation PPA with DFID CHASE is helping to address common challenges to peaceful state-society relations in fragile states, subnational conflict and post-conflict areas and transitional states at risk of renewed conflict. This activity represents programs in the Southern Philippines under the PPA during the period Jul-Sep 2012. These activities have the following objectives: 1) Formal peace processes and informal local peacebuilding efforts strengthened and more credible with conflict-affected populations; 2) Expanded community-level efforts to improve local security and relations with security forces (police, military).;

The Asia Foundation PPA with DFID CHASE is helping to address common challenges to peaceful state-society relations in fragile states, subnational conflict and post-conflict areas and transitional states at risk of renewed conflict. This activity represents analytical activities, including field research, surveys, and engagement with academics and practitioners. The purpose of these activities are to draw on the Foundation's field experience and knowledge to inform and influence aid practice and policy. This activity represents a range of regional programs during the period Apr-Jun 2012. ;
